												<div class="description author withsidebar">
													<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/lyz-lenz/">Lyz Lenz</a></h6>
													Lyz Lenz has been published in the <em>New York Times, Buzzfeed, Washington Post, The Guardian, ESPN, Marie Claire, Mashable, Salon</em>, and more. Her book <em>Belabored: Tales of Myth, Medicine, and Motherhood</em> is forthcoming. She also has an essay in the anthology <em>Not That Bad: Dispatches from Rape Culture</em> edited by Roxane Gay. Lenz holds an MFA in creative writing from Lesley University and is a contributing writer to the <em>Columbia Journalism Review</em>.																										<div class="website">
						    							<i class="fa fa-link"></i>
							    						<a href="http://www.lyzlenz.com/" target="_blank" class="external">http://www.lyzlenz.com/</a>
							    					</div>
							    																	</div>
											</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
										</div>

